-- Cheung Kong Infrastructure Prices $1 Billion of Perpetual Notes at 6.625%
-- B y   S h e l l e y   S m i t h
-- 2010-09-21T11:13:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/cheung-kong-infrastructure-prices-1-billion-of-perpetual-notes-at-6-625-.html
Cheung Kong Infrastructure
Holdings Ltd. priced $1 billion of perpetual notes, which are
callable after five years, to yield 6.625 percent according to a
person with knowledge of the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shelley Smith in Hong Kong at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
